  "analysis": "Now I understand the structure. doomgeneric_img.c includes my_stdlib.h which doesn't exist. Other doom source files include standard headers (<stdio.h>, <stdlib.h>, <string.h>, etc.). I need to: 1) Install MIPS cross-compiler, 2) Create my_stdlib.h and my_stdlib.c, 3) Create fake standard headers, 4) Create linker script and Makefile. The VM uses x86 syscall numbers via MIPS SYSCALL instruction with $v0 for syscall number and $a0-$a3 for args.",
  "plan": "First verify MIPS compiler is installed, then start creating the custom standard library and build system.",
  "commands": [
    {"keystrokes": "which mips-linux-gnu-gcc 2>/dev/null || (apt-get update && apt-get install -y gcc-mips-linux-gnu binutils-mips-linux-gnu)\n", "duration": 60.0},
    {"keystrokes": "grep -rn '#include' /app/doomgeneric/doomgeneric/*.c /app/doomgeneric/doomgeneric/*.h | grep '<' | sed 's/.*<//;s/>//' | sort -u\n", "duration": 0.1}
